        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 7:12PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 712 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Billings, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Billings, Lockwood, Billings West End and Crow Indian Reservation.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
